# DRAFT FOR ANALYST REVIEW — CVE-2026-62212
#
# Confidence: No public PoC known — pattern inferred from the
# CVE/advisory description only. No packet-capture (PCAP) data source
# is available to this pipeline — this pattern is NOT verified against
# captured exploit traffic.
#
# SEVERITY DISCREPANCY NOTE: NVD scores this CVE as CVSS 7.1 HIGH [1],
# while the CNA-published record on CVE.org scores it CVSS v4.0 5.1 MEDIUM [4].
# Analysts should review both scores before calibrating response priority.
#
# Detection rationale:
# CVE-2026-62212 involves a race condition in OpenClaw's MS Teams safeFetch
# DNS rebinding check [2][3]. A lower-trust caller can bypass authorization
# by exploiting timing windows in the safeFetch validation path. The observable
# network-layer behaviour most likely to be detectable is rapid, repeated HTTP
# requests to the safeFetch endpoint — a pattern consistent with timing-window
# exploitation (e.g., sending a benign request that passes the DNS rebinding
# check, then racing a follow-up request before validation completes).
# This rule alerts on a high request rate from a single source to paths
# containing "safeFetch" or "safe_fetch", which is the named vulnerable
# component per the advisory [3]. No specific wire format for the race
# condition payload is publicly documented; analysts should treat this
# pattern as a heuristic trip-wire only and tune the threshold to
# environment baseline before deployment.
#
# IMPORTANT LIMITATIONS:
# - The exact HTTP endpoint path is not confirmed in available sources;
#   "safeFetch" is inferred from the advisory title and description [2][3].
# - No exploit code, PCAP, or PoC is available to validate match logic.
# - Threshold values (count 6 / seconds 2) are approximations for
#   race-condition exploitation; adjust based on observed legitimate traffic.
# - is_kev is set to false — this CVE does not appear in the CISA KEV catalog
#   based on available context.

alert http $EXTERNAL_NET any -> $HOME_NET any (
  msg:"THREATFORGE CVE-2026-62212 OpenClaw safeFetch DNS rebinding auth bypass race attempt";
  flow:established,to_server;
  http.uri; content:"safeFetch"; nocase; fast_pattern;
  threshold:type both, track by_src, count 6, seconds 2;
  reference:cve,2026-62212;
  metadata:mitre_technique_id T1190, is_kev false, status experimental;
  classtype:attempted-recon;
  sid:9000004; rev:1; )

